<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2698] File Install Circular Configuration Update Loop</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2698</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using FileInstall 3.1.0, when I update a .cfg file, the system is sent into an infinite loop of updating the Configuration Admin Service and rewriting the cfg file.  The cycle goes something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Updated .cfg file is noticed by File Install DirectoryWatcher&lt;br/&gt;
2. The Configuration object is obtained and updated (in ConfigInstaller.setConfig(File))&lt;br/&gt;
3. The Configuration Admin Service fires a ConfigurationEvent&lt;br/&gt;
4. ConfigInstaller receives the ConfigurationEvent and writes out the new properties to the .cfg&lt;br/&gt;
5. Go to step 1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems like the ConfigInstaller object should figure out if the ConfigurationEvent is in response to an update to the .cfg file it just loaded.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One way to do this might be to put a &quot;special&quot; value in the Configuration that the ConfigurationListener method could look for.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another way would be to compare the configuration in the .cfg file to the properties that would normally be written.  If they&apos;re the same, don&apos;t write the file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
